data.title: Santa's behaviometer
data.statement:
Calvin is a good kid... At least that's what he likes to think.
This Christmas, like many other children around the world, Calvin is expecting an amazing present from Santa Claus.

However, this year Santa is kind of on a budget and can only afford to give presents to the [[G]] most deserving kids.
To select those Chosen Ones, Santa uses a device called the "Behaviometer". Given the name of a child, this device outputs a value based on how well they behaved this year.

Given the values outputted by the behaviometer for Calvin and other kids, print whether Calvin will or will not receive a gift this Christmas.

Note that since Santa has an overall positive image of Calvin, whenever there is a draw in the scores between Calvin and another kid, Calvin will be ranked <<higher>>.

lastVersion.statementHTML:
Goal

Calvin is a good kid... At least that's what he likes to think.
This Christmas, like many other children around the world, Calvin is expecting an amazing present from Santa Claus.

However, this year Santa is kind of on a budget and can only afford to give presents to the G most deserving kids.
To select those Chosen Ones, Santa uses a device called the "Behaviometer". Given the name of a child, this device outputs a value based on how well they behaved this year.

Given the values outputted by the behaviometer for Calvin and other kids, print whether Calvin will or will not receive a gift this Christmas.

Note that since Santa has an overall positive image of Calvin, whenever there is a draw in the scores between Calvin and another kid, Calvin will be ranked higher.
Input
Line 1: Two space-separated integers: the number of kids N (excluding Calvin) and the number of gifts G that Santa can afford to give this Christmas.
Line 2: An integer M, the mark given to Calvin by the behaviometer.
Lines 3 to 3+N: An integer Mi, the mark given to the i-th kid by the behaviometer.
Output
true if Calvin will receive a gift, false otherwise.
Constraints
0 ≤ N ≤ 2500
0 ≤ G ≤ N + 1
0 ≤ M ≤ 2147483647
0 ≤ Mi ≤ 2147483647
Example
Input
4 2
3
2
0
1
4
Output
true
